Pereon (
Fig. 1
) each pereonite with fine setae on proximo- and distolateral margins. Pereonite 1 shortest, 0.4 times as long as cephalothorax. Pereonites 2–6 distally convex. Pereonites 1–2 bearing two proximolateral setae and two distolateral setae. Pereonites 3–6 bearing one proximolateral seta and two disto-lateral setae. Pereonites 4–5 slightly longer than wide. Pereonites 3–5 equal in length and almost equal to width. Pereonite 6 distinctly shorter than pereonites 3–5 . Pereonites 1–6 proportional lengths 11.9 : 16.7 : 19.0: 19.0: 19.0: 14.4 .
